ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: The event name for which the data was collected
At any time in your child's life, did anyone use force to take something away from your child that he/she was carrying or wearing?
At any time in your child's life, did anyone steal something from your child and never give it back?  Things like a backpack, money, watch, clothing, bike, cell phone, computer, or anything else?
At any time in your child's life, did anyone break or ruin any of your child's things on purpose?

Sometimes people are attacked with sticks, rocks, guns, knives, or other things that could hurt.  At any time in your child's life, did anyone hit or attack your child on purpose with an object or weapon?  Somewhere like: at home, at school, at a store, in a car, on the street, or anywhere else?
At any time in your child's life, did anyone hit or attack your child WITHOUT using a weapon?
At any time in your child's life, did someone start to  attack your child, but for some reason it didn't happen?  For example, someone helped your child, or your child got away?
At any time in your child's life, did someone threaten to hurt your child when your child thought they might really do it?

When a person is kidnapped, it means they were made to go somewhere, like into a car, by someone whom they thought might hurt them.  At any time in your child's life, has anyone ever tried to kidnap your child?

At any time in your child's life, has your child been hit or attacked because of your child's skin color, religion, or where your child's family comes from?  Or because of a physical problem your child has?  Or because someone said your child was gay?
Sometimes groups of kids or gangs attack people.  At any time in your child's life, did a group of kids or a gang hit, jump, or attack your child?
At any time in your child's life, did any kid, even a brother or sister, hit your child?  Somewhere like: at home, at school, out playing, in a store, or anywhere else?
At any time in your child's life, did any kids try to hurt your child's private parts on purpose by hitting or kicking your child there?
At any time in your child's life, did any kids, even a brother or sister, pick on your child by chasing, or grabbing your child, or by making him/her do something he/she didn't want to do?

At any time in your child's life, did your child get really scared or feel really bad because kids were calling him/her names, saying mean things to him/her, or saying they didn't want your child around?
At any time in your child's life, did a boyfriend or girlfriend or anyone your child went on a date with slap or hit your child?
Notes: 1=Yes; 0=No; 98=I don't know; 99=I'd rather not say; 999=My child has never dated (not applicable)

ElementDescription: At any time in your child's life, did any kids ever tell lies or spread rumors about your child or try to make others dislike him/her?
At any time in your child's life, did any kids ever keep him/her out of things on purpose, exclude him/her from their group of friends, or completely ignore your child?
At any time in your child's life did your child SEE a parent get pushed, slapped, hit, punched, or beat up by another parent, or their boyfriend or girlfriend?
At any time in your child's life did your child SEE a parent hit, beat, kick, or physically hurt your child's brothers or sisters, not including a spanking on the bottom?
Notes: 1=Yes; 0=No; 98=I don't know; 99=I'd rather not say; 999=My child is an only child

ElementDescription: At any time in your child's life did your child SEE anyone get attacked or hit on purpose WITH a stick, rock, gun, knife, or other thing that would hurt?  Somewhere like: at home, at school, at a store, in a car, on the street, or anywhere else?
At any time in your child's life did your child SEE anyone get attacked or hit on purpose WITHOUT using a stick, rock, gun, knife, or other thing that would hurt?
At any time in your child's life, did anyone steal something from your house that belongs to your child's family or someone your child lives with?  Things like a TV, stereo, car, or anything else?
At any time in your child's life, was anyone close to your child murdered, like a friend, neighbor or someone in your child's family?
At any time in your child's life, was your child in any place in real life where he/she could see or hear people being shot, bombs going off, or street riots?
At any time in your child's life, was your child in the middle of a war where he/she could hear real fighting with guns or bombs?
At any time in your child's life, did anyone hurt or threaten him/her with a real gun?
At any time in your child's life, did he/she see someone else get hurt or threatened with a real gun?
Has your child ever gone to a school where someone said there was going to be a bomb or attack on the school and your child thought they might really mean it?

Has your child ever gone to a school where someone damaged the school or started a fire in the school on purpose?  Or did anyone break or ruin other school property like buses, windows, or sports equipment?
Has anyone ever used the <u>Internet</u> to bother or harass your child or to spread mean words or pictures about your child?
Has anyone ever used a <u>cell phone or texting</u> to bother or harass your child or to spread mean words or pictures about your child?
How many times did this happen to your child in his/her whole life?
How old was your child the first time this happened?
Did this happen in the last 12 months?
How old was your child the last time this happened?
Was your child physically hurt when this happened?  Hurt means you could still feel pain in your body the next day.  You are also hurt when you have a bruise, a cut that bleeds, or a broken bone.
Who did this? If there was more than one person, who was the most responsible?
Notes: 1=Brother, sister, or other child who lives with your child (cousin, foster sibling, etc.); 2=Biological or adoptive father; 3=Step-father or live-in boyfriend; 4=Biological or adoptive mother; 5=Step-mother or live-in girlfriend; 6=Foster parent; 7=A relative who lives in your child's home (uncle, grandparent, etc.); 8=A relative who does not live with your child; 9=A parent?s boyfriend, girlfriend, date, or ex-boyfriend or girlfriend who does not live with your child; 10=Grown-up your child knows from some organization, such as a teacher, coach, or youth group leader; 11=Anyone else your child knows such as a friend or neighbor or schoolmate; 12=Stranger (a stranger is someone your child doesn?t know); 13=Boyfriend/girlfriend, or ex-boyfriend/ex-girlfriend; 14=Other; 98=I don't know; 99=I'd rather not say
